<main>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">01</span> Introduction</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Cleer Money ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, stores, and discloses your personal information when you use the Cleer Money mobile application ("the App").</p>
    <p>We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth), the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs), and the Consumer Data Right (CDR) framework established under the <em>Competition and Consumer Act 2010</em> (Cth).</p>
    <p>By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Policy.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">02</span> Who We Are</h2>
    <p>Cleer Money is an Australian personal finance application operated by:</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Isaac Talbot</strong><br />
      Sole Trader, trading as Cleer Money<br />
      ABN: 99 498 576 599<br />
      Queensland, Australia
    </p>
    <p>We are not a bank, financial institution, or licensed financial adviser.</p>
    <p><strong>Contact:</strong><br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@cleermoney.com.au">privacy@cleermoney.com.au</a><br />
      Website: <a href="https://cleermoney.com.au">cleermoney.com.au</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">03</span> Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information:</strong> Your name and email address when you create an account.</li>
      <li><strong>Subscription information:</strong> Billing and subscription status (processed by Apple; we do not store payment card details).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Banking and Financial Data (via Open Banking / CDR)</h3>
    <p>With your explicit consent, we connect to your bank accounts using Australia's Consumer Data Right (CDR) framework via our accredited data recipient partner, <strong>Fiskil</strong>. Through this connection we may access:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your bank account names and identifiers</li>
      <li>Transaction history (up to 6 months of historical data)</li>
      <li>Transaction descriptions, amounts, dates, and merchant information</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We access only the data necessary to provide the App's core functionality. We do not access or store your internet banking login credentials.</p>

    <h3>App Usage Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Transaction categorisation choices you make within the App ("Want" / "Need" swipes)</li>
      <li>App settings and preferences</li>
      <li>Device type and operating system version (for troubleshooting)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technical Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Anonymised analytics data to help us understand how the App is used and to improve it</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">04</span> How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use your information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide, operate, and maintain the App and its features</li>
      <li>Connect to your bank accounts and retrieve transaction data with your consent</li>
      <li>Enable you to categorise and analyse your personal spending</li>
      <li>Send you relevant notifications about your finances (with your permission)</li>
      <li>Process and manage your subscription via Apple's in-app purchase system</li>
      <li>Respond to your enquiries and support requests</li>
      <li>Improve the App, diagnose technical issues, and ensure security</li>
      <li>Comply with our legal obligations</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="callout">
      We do <strong>not</strong> use your financial data for advertising, profiling, or on-selling purposes.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">05</span> Consumer Data Right — Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Cleer Money accesses your banking data under Australia's Consumer Data Right framework. In relation to CDR data:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>You control your consent.</strong> You can withdraw your consent to share banking data at any time through the App or directly via your bank's CDR dashboard.</li>
      <li><strong>Data minimisation.</strong> We only request the data necessary to operate the App. We do not request data beyond this scope.</li>
      <li><strong>Data retention.</strong> CDR data is retained for as long as you hold an active account. If you delete your account, CDR data is deleted within 7 days, except where retention is required by law.</li>
      <li><strong>No on-selling.</strong> Your CDR data is never sold, shared with advertisers, or used for secondary commercial purposes.</li>
      <li><strong>Accredited data recipient.</strong> Banking data is retrieved via Fiskil Pty Ltd, an accredited CDR data recipient. Fiskil's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://fiskil.com.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fiskil.com.au</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">06</span> Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Party</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Fiskil Pty Ltd</td><td>CDR-accredited data intermediary for bank connection</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Supabase Inc.</td><td>Cloud database and authentication infrastructure</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Apple Inc.</td><td>In-app subscription processing via App Store</td></tr>
          <tr><td>RevenueCat Inc.</td><td>Subscription status management</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Legal authorities</td><td>Where required by law, court order, or regulatory obligation</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>All third-party service providers are required to handle your data securely and only for the purposes we specify.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">07</span> Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>Your data is stored on Supabase infrastructure (hosted in Australia where available, otherwise in AWS data centres). We implement reasonable technical and organisational security measures including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Encryption of data in transit (TLS/HTTPS)</li>
      <li>Encryption of sensitive credentials at rest (using Supabase Vault)</li>
      <li>Row-level security controls on all database tables</li>
      <li>Access controls limited to authorised systems</li>
    </ul>
    <p>No method of electronic storage or transmission is 100% secure. While we take reasonable steps to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">08</span> Data Retention</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Retention Period</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Account information</td><td>Until account deletion, then deleted within 30 days</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Transaction data</td><td>Until account deletion, then deleted within 7 days</td></tr>
          <tr><td>CDR data</td><td>Until consent withdrawal or account deletion, then deleted within 7 days</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Subscription records</td><td>As required by Apple / RevenueCat and applicable tax law</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">09</span> Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Under the Australian Privacy Principles, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal information we hold about you</li>
      <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate or out-of-date personal information</li>
      <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and associated data</li>
      <li><strong>Withdraw CDR consent</strong> at any time without affecting your ability to continue using the App</li>
      <li><strong>Complain</strong> if you believe we have mishandled your information</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@cleermoney.com.au">privacy@cleermoney.com.au</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">10</span> Complaints</h2>
    <p>If you are not satisfied with our handling of a privacy complaint, you may contact the <strong>Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Website: <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oaic.gov.au</a></li>
      <li>Phone: 1300 363 992</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">11</span> Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is not directed at individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors. If you believe a minor has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will take steps to delete it.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="num">12</span> Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. For material changes, we will notify you via the App or by email. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Policy.</p>
  </section>

